definition.value: The S-(3-oxoadipyl) derivative of coenzyme A.
The S-(3-oxopalmitoyl) derivative of coenzyme A.
The S-(3-oxopimeloyl) derivative of coenzyme A.
A glycosylglucose consisting of a beta-L-fucosyl residue and an alpha-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A linear amino trisaccharide comprising of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue (1->3)-linked to a beta-D-galactosyl residue, which is in turn linked (1->4) to D-glucose.
A cholestanoyl-CoA formed by thioester linkage between 3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oic acid and coenzyme A.
A cholestanoyl-CoA formed by thioester linkage between 3alpha,7alpha-dihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oic acid and coenzyme A.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of alpha-D-galactofuranosyl and D-galactitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
